events.1637: Speculation in the tulip trade led to a first stock market crash
events.1609: The Bank of Amsterdam was established
events.1624: Rembrandt opens a studio in Leiden
events.1635: Death of son Rumbartus (2 moths old)
events.1636: Death of daughter Cornelia (3 weeks old)
events.1654: Had a daughter with his mistress
events.1656: Rembrandt was nearly bankrupt, had to sell his works
